descp2: int (optional) Stop early the construction of the tree at n_clusters. This is useful to decrease computation time if the number of clusters is not small compared to the number of samples. In this case, the complete tree is not computed, thus the 'children' output is of limited use, and the 'parents' output should rather be used. This option is valid only when specifying a connectivity matrix.
